---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Radio Disney Case Study - Idle Fusion"
  description="How we built Disney's mobile audio experience for young listeners, featuring live streaming, alarm clock integration, and seamless connections to the Disney ecosystem."
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="case-hero">
      <div class="case-container">
        <a href="/#our-work" class="back-link">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
            <path d="M16 10H4M4 10L9 5M4 10L9 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
          Back to Work
        </a>

        <div class="case-hero-content">
          <span class="case-category">Media & Entertainment</span>
          <h1 class="case-title">Radio Disney</h1>
          <p class="case-subtitle">A mobile audio experience that brought Disney magic to millions of young listeners — and paved the way for Disney's streaming future.</p>
          <span class="case-note">This app has since been retired as Disney consolidated its digital properties.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="case-meta">
          <div class="meta-item">
            <span class="meta-label">Client</span>
            <span class="meta-value">The Walt Disney Company</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <span class="meta-label">Industry</span>
            <span class="meta-value">Entertainment / Audio</span>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <span class="meta-label">Platform</span>
            <span class="meta-value">iOS & Android</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Challenge -->
    <section class="case-section">
      <div class="case-container">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="section-label">
            <span class="label-number">01</span>
            <span class="label-text">The Challenge</span>
          </div>
          <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Bringing radio to the smartphone generation</h2>
            <p>Radio Disney had a loyal audience of kids and families, but traditional radio was losing ground to on-demand digital content. Young listeners expected more than just audio — they wanted interactivity, personalization, and connection to the broader Disney universe.</p>
            <p>The challenge: reinvent the radio experience for mobile while maintaining the live, communal feel that made Radio Disney special — and strategically position the app as a gateway to Disney's growing digital ecosystem.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Approach -->
    <section class="case-section section-alt">
      <div class="case-container">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="section-label">
            <span class="label-number">02</span>
            <span class="label-text">Our Approach</span>
          </div>
          <div class="section-content">
            <h2>More than an app — a Disney experience</h2>
            <p>We designed and built a native mobile experience that went far beyond simple streaming:</p>
            <ul class="approach-list">
              <li><strong>Live streaming reimagined</strong> — Crystal-clear audio with real-time now-playing information, artist details, and interactive elements that made listeners feel connected to the broadcast</li>
              <li><strong>Radio Disney Alarm Clock</strong> — Wake up to your favorite Disney music. A beloved feature that let kids start their day with Radio Disney, driving daily app opens and habitual engagement</li>
              <li><strong>Disney ecosystem integration</strong> — Deep links to Disney Channel content, Disney apps, and eventually Disney+ — positioning Radio Disney as a discovery engine for Disney's entire content library</li>
              <li><strong>Social and interactive features</strong> — Song requests, shoutouts, and contests that brought the community feel of radio into the digital age</li>
              <li><strong>Parental trust</strong> — A safe, ad-appropriate experience that parents could hand to their kids without worry</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Results -->
    <section class="case-section">
      <div class="case-container">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="section-label">
            <span class="label-number">03</span>
            <span class="label-text">The Results</span>
          </div>
          <div class="section-content">
            <h2>A launchpad for Disney's digital future</h2>
            <div class="results-grid">
              <div class="result-card">
                <span class="result-number">Millions</span>
                <span class="result-label">of young listeners</span>
              </div>
              <div class="result-card">
                <span class="result-number">Daily</span>
                <span class="result-label">alarm clock engagement</span>
              </div>
              <div class="result-card">
                <span class="result-number">Gateway</span>
                <span class="result-label">to Disney ecosystem</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Radio Disney became more than a streaming app — it was a daily touchpoint with young Disney fans and a proving ground for cross-app content integration. The vertical integration patterns we built helped inform Disney's broader digital strategy as they moved toward consolidated streaming.</p>
            <p>While the app was eventually retired as Disney consolidated properties into Disney+, the work demonstrated how audio content could drive engagement and serve as a bridge to video and interactive experiences.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Legacy -->
    <section class="case-section section-alt">
      <div class="case-container">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="section-label">
            <span class="label-number">04</span>
            <span class="label-text">The Legacy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="section-content">
            <h2>Building for what comes next</h2>
            <p>The Radio Disney project exemplified a principle we still follow today: build not just for current requirements, but for where the industry is heading. The ecosystem integration patterns we pioneered — launching users seamlessly into related Disney content — anticipated the streaming consolidation that would define the next decade of entertainment.</p>
            <p>Sometimes the best measure of success isn't how long something lasts, but what it enables. Radio Disney helped millions of kids discover Disney content and helped Disney understand how mobile could unify their entertainment empire.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="case-cta">
      <div class="case-container">
        <h2>Building for an audience that matters?</h2>
        <p>We help media companies create experiences that engage, retain, and grow with their users.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Strategy Call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer variant="minimal" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .case-hero {
    padding: 8rem 0 4rem;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .case-container {
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .case-container {
      padding: 0 2rem;
    }
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .case-category {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: block;
  }

  .case-title {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .case-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  .case-note {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .case-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .meta-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .meta-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .meta-value {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .case-section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .section-alt {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
  }

  .section-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .section-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
  }

  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .label-number {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .label-text {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .section-content h2 {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .section-content p {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .approach-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .approach-list li {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .approach-list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.6em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .approach-list li strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .results-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .result-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .result-number {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .result-label {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .case-cta {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--ink);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .case-cta h2 {
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .case-cta p {
    font-family: 'Satoshi', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--paper);
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .dark .case-cta {
    background: #0a0a0a;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }
</style>
